---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
  description:
    "Call for Papers - UR-RAD 2025 AAAI Fall Symposium on Unifying Representations for Robot Application Development",
  title: "Call for Papers",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
  <h1 class="title mb-6">Call for Papers</h1>
  <div class="prose prose-citrus max-w-none px-4">
    <p class="text-lg mb-6">
      We invite submissions for the 3rd AAAI Fall Symposium on Unifying
      Representations for Robot Application Development.
    </p>

    <h2>Topics of Interest</h2>
    <p>Topics of interest include:</p>
    <ul
      class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 sm:grid sm:grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 lg:gap-x-8"
    >
      <li>Representational trends</li>
      <li>Representations for robot learning</li>
      <li>AI planning for robotics</li>
      <li>Formal methods in robotics</li>
      <li>Natural language as a representation</li>
      <li>Novel representations & novel representation uses</li>
      <li>Representations for user interfaces</li>
      <li>Robot end-user development</li>
      <li>Robot programming interfaces & paradigms</li>
      <li>Robot runtime/control environments</li>
      <li>Opportunities for standardization</li>
      <li>Frameworks (<em>e.g.</em>, ROS or middleware)</li>
      <li>Open-source & collaboration initiatives</li>
      <li>Identifying representation requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Submission Types</h2>
    <p>
      We invite the following contributions, formatted using the <a
        href="https://aaai.org/authorkit25/"
        class="citrus-link">AAAI-25 author kit</a
      >:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Full Papers (4-8 pages, archival OR non-archival):</strong> for novel
        research, artifact submissions, or strong works in progress.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Short Papers (2-4 pages, archival OR non-archival):</strong> for
        positions, smaller artifacts, and early work in progress.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Abstracts (1 page, non-archival only):</strong> for sharing ideas.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Submission Process</h2>
    <p>There are two submission rounds:</p>

    <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 bg-accent-base/5 rounded-lg mb-4">
      <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-2">
        Round 1 (Preferred)
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Submission Deadline:</strong> August 7, 2025</li>
        <li><strong>Camera Ready:</strong> August 29, 2025</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-2 text-xs sm:text-sm">
        Authors who want to be archived in the AAAI proceedings <strong
          >must</strong
        > submit their papers in the preferred round. Non-archival submissions are
        also heavily encouraged to submit during this round. Preferred submissions
        will be given preference for inclusion in the symposium in the event that
        a large number of paper submissions are received. If deemed necessary during
        the review phase, preferred submissions will also have an opportunity to
        revise their work based on reviewer feedback.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-3 sm:p-4 bg-special-lighter rounded-lg mb-6">
      <h3 class="text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Round 2 (Late)</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Short Abstract:</strong> August 7, 2025</li>
        <li><strong>Submission:</strong> August 22, 2025</li>
        <li><strong>Camera Ready:</strong> September 5, 2025</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Submit your paper <a
        href="https://easychair.org/my/conference?conf=fss25"
        class="citrus-link">here</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Intent to Submit</h2>
    <div class="mb-4 text-sm sm:text-base">
      <p class="mb-2">
        If you intend to submit a paper, please email us at <a
          href="mailto:urrad.symposium@gmail.com"
          class="citrus-link">urrad.symposium@gmail.com</a
        >.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2">
        Use the subject line: <strong>"[UR-RAD] Intent to Submit"</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="mb-2">Include in the body:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mb-2">
        <li>A tentative title</li>
        <li>A tentative author list</li>
        <li>Tentative keywords</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-accent-two">
        This step is optional, but will aid in our planning for reviewers. Note
        that at least one author from each paper will be expected to review 2-3
        UR-RAD papers themselves.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Review Process</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      We follow a double-anonymous review process (i.e. authors are unaware of
      reviewers' identity and reviewers are unaware of the authors' identity
      during the review process).
    </p>

    <h2>Important Dates Summary</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Symposium Date:</strong> November 6-8, 2025</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Location:</strong> Westin Arlington Gateway, Arlington, VA, USA
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Get in touch with us: <a
        href="mailto:urrad.symposium@gmail.com"
        class="citrus-link">urrad.symposium@gmail.com</a
      >
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
